If your page content is long enough (or the page size is small enough so it goes below the fold), clicking a link will move you to the correct position:

![Screen Shot 2020-04-14 at 17.41.05.png](PRACTICE%20Links%201902767ad7e381ee9174c2260377c933/Screen_Shot_2020-04-14_at_17.41.05.png)

Links can also perform actions outside of the Web browser: here's a link that uses the `mailto` protocol to send an email with your default email application:

```html
<a href="mailto:flavio@flaviocopes.com">email flavio</a>
```

Other applications can register their own protocols for internal use, to do something in an app when clicking a link in a browser.

